         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is concerned with a study of approximation order and construction of locally supported elements for the space S&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;4&lt;/sub&gt;(Δ) of C&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; pp (piecewise polynomial) functions on an arbitrary triangulation Δ of a connected polygonal domain Ω in R&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;. It is well known that even when Δ is a three-directional mesh Δ&lt;sup&gt;(1)&lt;/sup&gt;, the order of approximation of S&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;4&lt;/sub&gt;(Δ&lt;sup&gt;(1)&lt;/sup&gt;) is only 4, not 5. The objective of this paper is two-fold: (i) A local Clough-Tocher refinement procedure of an arbitrary triangulation Δ is introduced so as to yield the optimal (fifth) order of approximation, where locality means that only a few isolated triangles need refinement, and (ii) locally supported Hermite elements are constructed to achieve the optimal order of approximation.</p>
          </abstract>
